<h2>Declarative Component Adapter</h2>
<p>
    The Declarative Component Adapter is the intended implementation of the
    <a href="/blocks/component/">Component block</a> — the <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> element. It is a
    <strong>deterministic, build-time, AST-based transform</strong> that lowers each declarative
    definition into an equivalent class-based custom element plus
    <code>customElements.define()</code>. It is not a browser-side interpreter; nothing in the tier-1
    output depends on a runtime beyond baseline DOM APIs.
</p>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="status">Status</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Concept Phase.</strong> Sibling to the
        <a href="/adapters/functional-component-adapter/">Functional Component Adapter</a> (functional → class) and
        in the lineage of the canonical <a href="/adapters/html-adapter/">HTML Adapter</a>'s
        AST-transformation work. Whether it stays standalone or folds into the HTML Adapter is an
        open point (<strong>DC-6</strong>, see the
        <a href="/blocks/component/#open-questions">Component block</a>).
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="concept">Concept</h3>
    <p>The transform takes declarative markup in:</p>
    {% highlight "html" %}
<component name="user-card" shadow="open">
  <template>
    <style>:host { display: block }</style>
    <h3><slot name="title">Untitled</slot></h3>
    <slot></slot>
  </template>
</component>
    {% endhighlight %}
    <p>…and deterministically emits the class form out:</p>
    {% highlight "typescript" %}
const TEMPLATE = document.createElement('template');
TEMPLATE.innerHTML =
  `<style>:host { display: block }</style>` +
  `<h3><slot name="title">Untitled</slot></h3><slot></slot>`;

class UserCard extends HTMLElement {
  connectedCallback() {
    const root = this.shadowRoot ?? this.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });
    if (!root.childNodes.length) root.append(TEMPLATE.content.cloneNode(true));
  }
}
customElements.define('user-card', UserCard);
    {% endhighlight %}
    <p>
        The class name is derived from <code>name</code> (kebab → PascalCase); <code>shadow</code>
        selects the <code>attachShadow</code> mode (or light DOM for <code>none</code>); the
        <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> becomes the cloned render source. This is the same lowering
        Svelte's compiler and Lit-style tooling already perform.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="guarantees">Determinism guarantees</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Byte-identical output</strong> for identical input — stable member ordering, no timestamps or content hashes — so generated files diff cleanly and cache well.</li>
        <li><strong>AST-based, not string-rewriting</strong> — the definition is parsed to an AST and emitted from the AST; source is never regex-patched.</li>
        <li><strong>Zero residual runtime (tier 1)</strong> — output uses only baseline <code>attachShadow</code>, <code>&lt;template&gt;.content.cloneNode</code>, and <code>customElements.define()</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Idempotent registration</strong> — the emitted <code>connectedCallback</code> no-ops if the tree is already populated (SSR / Declarative Shadow DOM hydration safe).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        The deterministic, AST-based emitter could be built on the workspace's existing
        esbuild / TypeScript tooling. Concrete code lives in the reference implementation
        (Frontier UI), not in this canonical repo.
    </p>
</section>

